## 7. Milestones (definition-of-done per tier)

- **P0 — "CPython boots and prints."** exit/exit_group, mmap/munmap/mprotect/brk, read/write/openat/close/fstat/getdents64/lseek, clock_gettime, getrandom, getuid family, set_tid_address, rt_sigaction/procmask, rseq→ENOSYS. **DoD:** `python -c "print(2+2)"` and `import fastapi` succeed inside the guest.
- **P1 — "serve one request."** epoll_create1/ctl/wait, socket/bind/listen/accept4/recvfrom/sendto/connect/setsockopt/getsockopt, pipe2/eventfd2, fcntl, readv/writev, nanosleep. **DoD:** a FastAPI app returns 200 to one real HTTP request end-to-end.
- **P2 — "production-ish single instance."** snapshot pre-init (1 ms cold start), DNS resolver + egress policy, statx/dup/poll/select, mkdir/unlink/rename, AF_UNIX, metering hooks (epoch/fuel). **DoD:** existing FastAPI+pydantic+httpx+SQLAlchemy-over-your-Postgres app deploys unchanged, cold-starts <5 ms, meters CPU-ms.
- **P3 — "scale/compat tail."** real threads (futex + shared memory), fork/clone/wait4 via CoW, live migration across machines/arch. **DoD:** an app using a thread pool and one that forks both run; drain-migrate a live instance x86→ARM.

